    • ModelObject

      public ModelObject​(org.json.JSONObject jObj)
      Constructs a complete ModelObject from the key/value pairs present in JSONObject. Not all fields map to the ModelObject fields so that inherited classes can make use of ModelObject construction through the super constructor
      Parameters:
      jObj - - Well formatted JSONObject

    • ModelObject

      public ModelObject​(ModelObject mObj) throws org.json.JSONException
      Copies a model object into a new one with a shallow copy of the ModelObject field attributes only. May not want to use this class as it is not fully tested
      Parameters:
      mObj - - Modelobject to be copied
      Throws:
      org.json.JSONException - - JSON super error.

    • GetString

      public java.lang.String GetString​(java.lang.String Key)
      Returns the JSONObject key as a string. User should generally be aware of whether the internal key value is a string otherwise the exception case is silently handled and an empty string is returned
      Parameters:
      Key - - JSON Object key
      Returns:
      String value from key or empty string

    • getChildren

      public org.json.JSONObject getChildren​(java.lang.String Pluralized)
      Gets the children JSONObject from this ModelObject. ModelObjects store children models by their pluralized names i.e. (Pages). This key is searched for a the resulting JSONObject is returned
      Parameters:
      Pluralized - - pluralized Model class key
      Returns:
      - JSONObject for child element
